<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04586</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING RACIAL, ETHNIC AND RELIGIOUS DISCRIMINATION</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines several terms among others such as ETHNIC ORIGIN, ETHNO LINGUISTIC GROUP, INDIGENOUS PEOPLES,
STEREOTYPE/STEREOTYPING, et.al.

Provides for several ACTS OF DISCRIMINATION which are deemed discriminatory and shall be prohibited: 
discrimination in : political participation; employment; education and training; delivery of goods and services; land, business and other accommodation; access to public places, facilities, and public meetings; advertisements/mass media; discrimination : by wrongful portrayal; through speech, utterances, acts of hatred and similar act, through analogous acts that result in impairment of the enjoyment of human rights and fundamental freedoms; through engaging in profiling; and through abuses of state and non - state actors.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BELMONTE, JOSE CHRISTOPHER Y.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-12</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Savellano (000 2019-10-23)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HUMAN RIGHTS ON 2019-09-16</td></tr></table>